{"id": 223677098, "title": "Gov. Namadi Inspects Housing Projects Amid Commitment To Quality", "text": "Governor Umar Namadi of Jigawa state over the weekend embarked on a series of inspection visits to mass housing project sites across major cities in the state. A press statement by Hajiya Zainab Rabo Ringim, the Senior Special Assistant media Affairs that was made available to newsmen said the move is a demonstration of his dedication to delivering on his campaign promises. The Senior Special Assistant media Affairs further stated that in addition \u201cThis bold move is aimed at ensuring the quality of work and timely completion of the projects, which are a key component of his 12-point agenda.\u201d The statement noted that \u201cThe mass housing units are designed to provide a conducive living environment for state workers, enhancing their productivity and overall well-being.\u201d Hajiya Zainab Rabo Ringim, explained that \u201cBy inspecting the projects firsthand, Governor Namadi is able to assess the progress made so far, identify challenges, and intervene where necessary to guarantee the successful completion of the projects.\u201d She revealed that \u201cDuring his visits, the Governor commended some contractors for their excellent work while cautioning others with subpar performance, including the Gumel town project.\u201d According to the statement \u201cThis proactive approach demonstrates his commitment to accountability and transparency in governance.\u201d She disclosed that \u201cThe provision of housing units is a critical aspect of Governor Namadi\u2019s agenda, aimed at promoting socio-economic development and enhancing service delivery across all sectors. \u201c By prioritizing the welfare of state workers, he is fostering a more efficient and effective workforce, ultimately benefiting the citizens of the state, the statement reads.", "summary": "<div style=\"margin-bottom:20px;\"><img width=\"586\" height=\"375\" src=\"https://independent.ng/wp